  Hindustan Petroleum Corp. (HPCL) ,  India ’s
third-largest state refiner, is seeking to buy crude cargoes of
as much as 1 million barrels each for loading in late-December
or early January, according to a tender document obtained by
Bloomberg News.  The tender was issued Dec. 16 and follows a similar request
for sweet crudes that was sent on Dec. 13 for cargoes loading in
early February.  Details of the company’s requirement are as follow:  To contact the reporter on this story:
